{"questionId":"21345","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Professor Wei observed that students have difficulty remembering the information presented&nbsp;in his lectures.</p>\n<p>He modelled the percentage of information retained, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi></math>, by the function <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>100</mn><msup><mtext>e</mtext><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi>p</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></msup></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>≥</mo><mn>0</mn></math>,&nbsp;where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math> is the number of days after the lecture.</p>\n<p>He found that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn></math> day after a lecture, students had forgotten <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>50</mn><mo>%</mo></math> of the information presented.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Based on his model, Professor Wei believes that his students will always retain some&nbsp;information from his lecture.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>State a mathematical reason why Professor Wei might believe this.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi><mfenced><mi>t</mi></mfenced><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; <strong>OR&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi><mfenced><mi>t</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp;has&nbsp;a horizontal asymptote&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp;R1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><br>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"21345","referenceCode":"21M.1.SL.TZ1.7c","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"State a mathematical reason why Professor Wei might believe this.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.5—Modelling functions"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}